{"parse":{"title":"Lionel de Fonseka","pageid":38294914,"revid":856049843,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-style ambox-Orphan\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"display: none\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Wiki_letter_w.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Wiki letter w.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/40px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/60px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/80px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"44\" data-file-height=\"44\" /></a></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>is an <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Orphan\" title=\"Wikipedia:Orphan\">orphan</a>, as no other articles <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Whatlinkshere&amp;target=Lionel_de_Fonseka&amp;namespace=0\">link to it</a></b>. Please <a href=\"/wiki/Help:Link\" title=\"Help:Link\">introduce links</a> to this page from <span class=\"plainlinks\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special%3ASearch&amp;redirs=1&amp;search=Lionel+de+Fonseka&amp;fulltext=Search&amp;ns0=1&amp;title=Special%3ASearch&amp;advanced=1&amp;fulltext=Lionel+de+Fonseka\">related articles</a></span>; try the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//edwardbetts.com/find_link?q=Lionel_de_Fonseka\">Find link tool</a> for suggestions.  <small><i>(January 2013)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table><p><b>Lionel de Fonseka</b> or <b>Fonseka-Varnasuriya</b> (born 27 October 1889<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ceylon_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ceylon-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>) was a <a href=\"/wiki/Sinhala_people\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sinhala people\">Sinhalese</a> writer and art critic, best known for <i>On the Truth of Decorative Art</i> (1912).\n</p><h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Life\">Life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lionel_de_Fonseka&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lionel de Fonseka was educated at <a href=\"/wiki/Royal_College,_Colombo\" title=\"Royal College, Colombo\">Royal College, Colombo</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Oxford_University\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Oxford University\">Oxford University</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ceylon_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ceylon-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> where he knew <a href=\"/wiki/Alain_Locke\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Alain Locke\">Alain Locke</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> <i>De la Verit\u00e9 dans l'art</i> - subsequently translated into English as <i>On the Truth of Decorative Art</i> (1912) - argued against the corruption of Sinhalese art by Western influence:\n</p>\n<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r856303468\">.mw-parser-output .templatequote{overflow:hidden;margin:1em 0;padding:0 40px}.mw-parser-output .templatequote .templatequotecite{line-height:1.5em;text-align:left;padding-left:1.6em;margin-top:0}</style><blockquote class=\"templatequote\"><p>Sinhalese art has hitherto been strictly decorative; and as a Sinhalese I view with regret the modern tendency in Ceylon, under Western influences, to abandon our traditions in art and in life. It seems to me that Eastern peoples need to realize at the least that art, education, civilization, admit of a plural; also that what is fortuitously predominant is not necessarily intrinsically excellent. It is regrettable that the rise of Western commerce should involve the decline of Eastern art; but though regrettable, it is not inevitable.\n</p></blockquote>\n<p>According to his nephew, de Fonseka wrote the book \"primarily to satisfy his father, that he was using his time to good purpose\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> However, the book is said to have influenced <a href=\"/wiki/Ananda_Coomaraswamy\" title=\"Ananda Coomaraswamy\">Ananda Coomaraswamy</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Eric_Gill\" title=\"Eric Gill\">Eric Gill</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Romain_Rolland\" title=\"Romain Rolland\">Romain Rolland</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Gunawardena2005_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Gunawardena2005-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In April 1913 Fonseka, <a href=\"/wiki/Arthur_Ransome\" title=\"Arthur Ransome\">Arthur Ransome</a>, Coomaraswamy, <a href=\"/wiki/Anthony_Ludovici\" title=\"Anthony Ludovici\">Anthony Ludovici</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Lascelles_Abercrombie\" title=\"Lascelles Abercrombie\">Lascelles Abercrombie</a> entered into controversy in the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Academy_(magazine)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Academy (magazine)\">Academy</a></i> over who had priority in using the phrase \"Art for life's sake\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> De Fonseka entered into fashionable London life, attending a King's Lev\u00e9e at <a href=\"/wiki/Buckingham_Palace\" title=\"Buckingham Palace\">Buckingham Palace</a> on 3 June 1913.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>De Fonseka subsequently lived and worked in <a href=\"/wiki/France\" title=\"France\">France</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Belgium\" title=\"Belgium\">Belgium</a> for over a decade. He donated a gold chalice to <a href=\"/wiki/Bruges_Cathedral\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bruges Cathedral\">Bruges Cathedral</a>. After a pilgrimage to <a href=\"/wiki/F%C3%A1tima,_Portugal\" title=\"F\u00e1tima, Portugal\">F\u00e1tima, Portugal</a>, he wrote an account of the <a href=\"/wiki/Marian_apparitions\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Marian apparitions\">Marian apparitions</a> believed to have taken place at <a href=\"/wiki/Cova_da_Iria\" title=\"Cova da Iria\">Cova da Iria</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Working as a barrister in Ceylon,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ceylon_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ceylon-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Fonseka was a contributor to the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Daily_News_(Sri_Lanka)\" title=\"Daily News (Sri Lanka)\">Daily News</a></i> there,<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> as well as writing a weekly column for the <i>Ceylon Catholic Messenger</i>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Works\">Works</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lionel_de_Fonseka&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Works\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><i>De la verit\u00e9 dans l'art</i>, Paris, 1912. Translated as <i>On the Truth of Decorative Art: A Dialogue between an Oriental and an Occidental</i>, London: Greening, 1912.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> Published with an introduction by Ananda Coomaraswamy in 1913.</li>\n<li>'China Sunday!', <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_New_Age\" title=\"The New Age\">The New Age</a></i>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dl.lib.brown.edu/pdfs/1140814199906070.pdf\">vol. 13, no. 1</a> (1 May 1913), p.&#160;9.</li>\n<li>'Futurism in Food', <i>The New Age</i>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dl.lib.brown.edu/pdfs/1140814207532014.pdf\">vol. 13. no. 6</a> (5 June 1913), pp.&#160;148\u2013149.</li>\n<li>'The White Dancer', <i>The New Age</i>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dl.lib.brown.edu/pdfs/1140814246382174.pdf\">vol. 14. no. 3</a> (20 November 1913), pp.&#160;76\u201378.</li>\n<li>'A Thinking Man', <i>The New Age</i>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dl.lib.brown.edu/pdfs/1140814260105227.pdf\">vol. 14. no. 8</a> (25 December 1913), pp.&#160;238\u20139.</li>\n<li>'War and the Aesthete', <i>The New Age</i>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dl.lib.brown.edu/pdfs/1140814344294309.pdf\">vol. 16, no. 9</a> (31 December 1914), pp.&#160;216\u201317.</li>\n<li>'The Karave Flag', <i>Ceylon Antiquary and Literary Register</i>, Vol. Ill, Part I (July, 1921), pp.&#160;1\u201311.</li>\n<li><i>Les eaux de lumi\u00e8re: dialogue entre un Oriental et un Occidental</i> (The waters of life: dialogue between an oriental and an occidental), Monaco: \u00c9ditions de Fontvieille, 1953.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lionel_de_Fonseka&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ceylon-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Ceylon_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Ceylon_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Ceylon_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>Ceylon, its history, people, commerce, industries and resources</i>, 1924, p.28.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Jeffrey Green, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.jeffreygreen.co.uk/alain-locke-black-rhodes-scholar-at-oxford-1907-1910\">Alain Locke, black Rhodes Scholar at Oxford 1907-1910</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.defonseka.com/pe0016.htm\">De la Verit\u00e9 dans l'Art</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Gunawardena2005-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Gunawardena2005_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Charles A. Gunawardena (2005). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=hWLQSMPddikC&amp;pg=PA104\"><i>Encyclopedia Of Sri Lanka</i></a>. Sterling Publishers Pvt. Ltd. p.&#160;104. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-932705-48-5\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-1-932705-48-5\">978-1-932705-48-5</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">22 January</span> 2013</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Encyclopedia+Of+Sri+Lanka&amp;rft.pages=104&amp;rft.pub=Sterling+Publishers+Pvt.+Ltd&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.isbn=978-1-932705-48-5&amp;rft.au=Charles+A.+Gunawardena&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DhWLQSMPddikC%26pg%3DPA104&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALionel+de+Fonseka\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\"Art for Life's Sake\", <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Manchester_Guardian\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Manchester Guardian\">The Manchester Guardian</a></i>, 26 April 1913.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span